quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  83,35,"seated on raised benches, they look on"
  83,36,Were the ones who are ungrateful not rewarded for what they had been accomplishing
  84,1,When the heaven was split open
  84,2,and gave ear to its Lord as it will be justly disposed to do
  84,3,and when the earth stretches out
  84,4,and cast what is in it and voided itself
  84,5,and gave ear to its Lord as it will be justly disposed to do
  84,6,"O human being! Truly, thou art one who is laboring towards thy Lord laboriously and thou wilt be one who encounters Him"
  84,7,And as for him who will be given his book in his right hand
  84,8,"then, he will be made a reckoning, an easy reckoning"
  84,9,and will turn about to his people as one who is joyous
  84,10,But for whoever will be given his book behind his back
  84,11,he will call for damnation
  84,12,and roast in a blaze
  84,13,He had been one who is joyous with his people
  84,14,"Truly, he thought he would never retreat"
  84,15,"Yea! Truly, his Lord had been seeing him"
  84,16,So no! I swear an oath by the twilight
  84,17,and by the night and whatever it enveloped
  84,18,and by the moon when it was full
  84,19,"that you will, truly, ride plane after plane"
  84,20,"Then, what is for them who believe not"
  84,21,"when the Quran was recited to them, they prostrate not themselves?â€¡"
  84,22,Nay! Those who were ungrateful deny
  84,23,but God is greater in knowledge of what they amass
  84,24,So give them good tidings of a painful punishment
  84,25,"But those who believed and did as the ones in accord with morality, for them is compensation, that which is unfailing"